section.section:
The warrant shall:
identify the item or type of property to be seized;
state the grounds for its issuance and the name of the affiant;
require the person to whom the warrant is directed to inspect the area, premises, building, or conveyance identified for the specified purpose;
require, where appropriate, the seizure of the specified property;
require that the warrant be served during normal business hours; and
designate the judge to whom the warrant is to be returned.
